Huawei has revealed its new smart glasses in collaboration with Gentle Monster. The company announced the new wearable device at its P30 media event in Paris. The smart glasses do not have any cameras, but do sport dual microphones as well as built-in speakers and voice assistant support. Users can control the smart glasses by touching the side of the frames, and the wearable also supports wireless charging inside a dedicated case â€“ as well as IP67 water and dust resistance. There is currently no pricing information available for the glasses, but they will be available in mid-2019 in various models. Huawei said the new smart glasses could be available in South Africa from July 2019.